AD-FTD Structure‑Function Analysis

MATLAB and R code for the analyses in Functional Network Collapse in Neurodegenerative Disease (Brown et al., 2025).

Overview
This repository contains code for:
- Partial‑least‑squares (PLS) analysis linking regional atrophy to functional connectivity.
- Syndrome‑specific FC patterns and reconstructions from PLS components.
- Regression of functional PLS components on gradient covariance.
- Coupled‑oscillator simulations of gradient dynamics and eigenmode analyses.


System requirements:
Software dependencies
Matlab (tested on R2022b)
MATLAB toolboxes: Statistics & Machine Learning; Signal Processing
External MATLAB packages: CircStat 2012a (included)
R studio (Version 2022.12.0+353)

Installation guide:
Start MATLAB and run:
cd adftd_structure_function
startup          % adds sub‑folders to MATLAB path

Typical install time: < 2 minutes

Demo:
Data: 
- for Matlab, all necessary data is stored in adftd_structure_function_data.mat. Run adftd_structure_function.m script.
- for R, all necessary data is in cognition_data/*. Run cognition_gam.R script.
Expected output: 
- for Matlab, key figures, print outs, and new variables
- for R, GAM F statistics and p-values for each neuropsych model.
Expected run time: < 5 minutes

Instructions for use:
How to run the software on your data: 
- get atrophy and functional connectivity matrices, feed into PLS
- get gradient projections, coupling parameters, eigenmodes: TBD
Reproduction instructions: see above


